<title>SOUTH AFRICA: CIC Holdings raises half year shr.</title>
<headline>CIC Holdings raises half year shr.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended December 31.</p>
<p>			(million N$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     23.1	  vs   18.2</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   15.4	  vs   10.0</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   19.6	  vs   11.1</p>
<p>    Tax			  3.5	  vs    1.9</p>
<p>    Turnover		 882.1	  vs  308.0</p>
<p>    Full name:   CIC Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>    Extraordinary items     -	   vs   (0.8)</p>
<p>NOTE - The directors declared an interim dividend of 2.5 cents per share, payable around April 18 to shareholders registered on March 27.</p>
<p>NOTE(2) - The group said heavy rains and major new agency representations in Namibia and Botwsana would benefit business in the second half. It said the fishing industry was showing signs of recovery and operational efficiencies were being implemented on subsidiaries which have so far not performed to expectation.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom 27 11 482 1003</p>
